{"link":"https://trailhead.salesforce.com/en/modules/get_ready_for_dreamforce_become_salesforce_speaker/units/get_ready_for_dreamforce_sf_speaker_present_like_a_pro","title":"Present Like a Pro Unit | Salesforce Trailhead","shortLink":"get_ready_for_dreamforce_sf_speaker_present_like_a_pro","questions":[{"title":"1Generally, what is the best way to practice your presentation?","answers":[{"content":"A Run through the presentation only once, because you don\u0027t want to look too rehearsed on stage.","selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(1) \u003e div.question_answer.clearfix:nth-child(2)"},{"content":"B Rehearse for as many hours as possible the day before your presentation.","selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(1) \u003e div.question_answer.clearfix:nth-child(3)"},{"content":"C Practice in front of an audience, and ask them for feedback.","selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(1) \u003e div.question_answer.clearfix:nth-child(4)"}],"wrongAnswers":[{"content":"D Always have a full script that includes everything you\u0027re going to say.","selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(1) \u003e div.question_answer.clearfix:nth-child(5)"}],"correctAnswer":{"content":"C Practice in front of an audience, and ask them for feedback.","selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(1) \u003e div.question_answer.clearfix:nth-child(4)"},"selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(1)"},{"title":"2Which of the following statements is true?","answers":[{"content":"B If something goes wrong during your presentation your audience will begin to doubt your expertise.","selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(2) \u003e div.question_answer.clearfix:nth-child(3)"},{"content":"D All presenters encounter the unexpected at some point. Relax and acknowledge what happened, and keep going.","selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(2) \u003e div.question_answer.clearfix:nth-child(5)"}],"wrongAnswers":[{"content":"C Problems are a sign you didn\u0027t prepare well.","selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(2) \u003e div.question_answer.clearfix:nth-child(4)"},{"content":"A Seasoned speakers never have problems during presentations.","selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(2) \u003e div.question_answer.clearfix:nth-child(2)"}],"correctAnswer":{"content":"D All presenters encounter the unexpected at some point. Relax and acknowledge what happened, and keep going.","selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(2) \u003e div.question_answer.clearfix:nth-child(5)"},"selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(2)"},{"title":"3Which of the following is a presentation best practice?","answers":[{"content":"A Always stand behind the podium. People get distracted by any movement.","selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(3) \u003e div.question_answer.clearfix:nth-child(2)"},{"content":"B Make sustained eye contact with different people in your audience, because this will help them connect with what you\u0027re saying.","selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(3) \u003e div.question_answer.clearfix:nth-child(3)"},{"content":"C Use lots of filler words, because they make you seem more relatable.","selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(3) \u003e div.question_answer.clearfix:nth-child(4)"},{"content":"D Speak quickly, because you can cover more material in your presentation that way.","selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(3) \u003e div.question_answer.clearfix:nth-child(5)"}],"wrongAnswers":[],"correctAnswer":{"content":"B Make sustained eye contact with different people in your audience, because this will help them connect with what you\u0027re saying.","selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(3) \u003e div.question_answer.clearfix:nth-child(3)"},"selector":"#challenge \u003e section.challenge-section.challenge-section-container.quiz \u003e div.bottom-section \u003e div.questions \u003e div.question:nth-child(3)"}]}